objectives.en:
The objectives of the course are to:
- introduce the basic concepts of machine learning with a focus on neural networks and deep learning, including neural network building blocks, key algorithms and commonly used architectures;
- illustrate the design considerations in building and training an effective deep neural network through specific examples;
- introduce the domain specific considerations that arise in the application of deep neural networks for the study of molecular biology systems, with applications in protein analysis, synthetic biology, drug design and related fields;
- provide practical classes complementary to the lecture topics to enable students to experience directly how to train and apply deep neural networks to specific problems;
- provide sufficient background to enable students to continue with more specialised topics in deep learning, especially with applications in molecular biology.

learning_outcomes.en:
At the end of the course, students should:
- have acquired an understanding of the major concepts in machine learning and around the use of deep neural networks in particular, and of the practical considerations related to building and using such models; in general terms as well as with domain specific considerations for molecular biology;
- be able to write clear and well-argued descriptions of these topics, based on the course material and relevant literature from the suggested reading lists;
- be able to design appropriate training data sets and train and apply simple deep neural networks on a range of data types in molecular biology;
- be able to continue the study of deep neural networks for applications in molecular biology through research projects.
